<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-07-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="89" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>, chargé,
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-07-24"><hi rend="italic">July 24,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Have received a telegram from the U. S. minister in Japan with reference
                            to taking Japanese citizens under the protection of the United States in
                            case of war. Chinese Government has given consent and asks the United
                            States to protect Chinese in Japan. A reply is requested.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>